    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-11T19:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-11T19:30:00-05:00" n="463"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.3715/46: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-11T20:00:00-04:30"
                            >May 11, 1937—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>621. Department’s 328, May 11, 1 a.m. The first detachment of 64 Cuban refugees
                    left Madrid for Alicante this morning. The second group of about 60 will leave
                    tomorrow morning. Vice Consul Wells will proceed to Alicante Thursday to lend
                    assistance toward expediting evacuation formalities. If no difficulties arise
                    the <hi rend="italic">Raleigh</hi> should be able to depart before noon on the
                    14th.</p>
                <p>In addition to the Cubans there will be 4 Guatemalan women and their 4 children,
                    1 Mexican woman, and 1 American negro (See last paragraph of telegram No. X–552,
                    March 16, 10 a.m.<note n="67" xml:id="d463fn67">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_497">p. 497</ref>.</note>) The
                    latter is destitute.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
